            <h2 class="text-center">Programs</h2>
            <hr><br/>
            <!-- <img src="http://placehold.it/300x300" alt="helping others collage"> -->
            <h3>High School Visitation (HSV)</h3>
              <p>
                High school visitation is one of SHPE's defining programs, bringing more and more young latinos into the areas of STEM.We bring high school students to U of I and show them exactly what its like to be an engineering student. We have them do experiments and challanges. A lot of the time these students return to the U of I and become fully fledged engineers. The Fall HSV mainly focuses on underpriviliged and at risk youths in the state of Illinois. The Spring HSV has everyone who got accepted into the University of Illinois come and take a look at the university.  
              </p>
            <h3>Visiting High Schools</h3>
              <p>
                Visiting High Schools has been a great way of spreading STEM awareness. Every year several SHPE members go out to High Schools across Urbana-Champaign and demo several experiments to get the students interested in Science and Engineering. 
              </p>  
            <h3>Shadow Program</h3>
              <p>
                Much like Shadow Programs with companies, the SHPE shadow program take a High School student and pairs them with a University student who takes them through their day showing them what its like being an engineering student. 
              </p>  
